sally embrey jenna davis phd search search this site stanford university jenna davis phd assistant professor dept of civil and environmental engineering higgins magid fellow woods institute for the environment sally embrey navigation research meet the poop group cv & press teaching w&s resources w&s scholarships & fellowships contact home meet the poop group sally embrey sally is a new graduate student in the environmental engineering & science program within the department of civil & environmental engineering though she is currently working on her masters degree she is planning on staying for a phd sally has been fortunate to work on a variety of health initiatives in every continent except antarctica in particular her work as an environmental emergency responder in nigeria lead her to stanford where she wants to gain experience in applied health interventions she is particularly interested in studying water and sanitation interventions and their relationship to infectious disease outcomes in areas affected by climate change her research with the poop group is likely to focus on the availability of microcredits for water and sanitation investments in kenya and how these credits change household economics health and behavior sally earned a dual msph in epidemiology and environmental health from emory university and a bs in biomedical science from colorado state university outside of research sally likes to spend her time in the mountains skiing or cycling sometimes she also gets the change to use the right side her brain and enjoys creating stained glass windows painting and sewing last modified mon 31 oct 2011 at 15 11 login stanford university all rights reserved stanford ca 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
